commit.message: added long description to setup

Syntax fix: For regexes, replace unicode strings with raw strings

This adresses some hundreds of `DeprecationWarning` from `pywhois`,
when used in a project of mine. They ware variations of:

     DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence \.
     DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence \w
     DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence \s
     # and possibly others ...

This should prepare `pywhois` for a these being upped to printed
SyntaxWarnings and later SyntaxErrors, as per:
https://bugs.python.org/issue32912
